cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the representation of graphs using orthogonal polygons and visibility, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The study of combinatorial properties of configurations in graphs is related to graph theory (cs.GT) and the use of integer grids and drawing algorithms is related to computational complexity (cs.DS) and computer graphics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the complexity of the representation, which is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
